FBIS4-52978 "dreas095_c_94009" FBIS-EAS-94-095 Daily Report 15 May 1994 North Korea Students Demand Investigation of Kwangju Incident Students Demand Investigation of Kwangju Incident SK1505091394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0838 GMT 15 May 94 SK1505091394 Pyongyang KCNA English BFN [Text] Pyongyang, May 15 (KCNA) -- Some 800 students affiliated with the South Korean Federation of General Student Councils (Hanchongnyon) held a rally at Hanyang campus on May 14 demanding the investigation into the Kwangju massacre and the punishment of those responsible for it, a Seoul-based radio reported. Noting that the truth behind the massacre has not yet been made clear, the ralliers strongly demanded the punishment of those responsible for it including two former "presidents," Chon Tu-hwan and No Tae-u. After the rally, they went out of the campus demanding the "government"-level investigation and the punishment of the culprits.
